Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Given an array of integers target, return an array result consisting of all elements target[i] that are greater than both of their neighbors, i.e., elements that satisfy the condition:

target[i] > max(target[i−1], target[i+1])

Note: The first and the last elements are included by default in the result array because they do not have two neighbors.

Input Format
The input consists of multiple test cases.

The first line contains a single integer T, the number of test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains an integer n, the length of the array.

The second line contains n space-separated integers representing the elements of target.

Output Format
For each test case, output the result array for the corresponding target array on a new line.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 100
1 ≤ n ≤ 100
−100 ≤ target[i] ≤ 100

Sample Input 1
1
5
1 3 1 3 2

Sample Output 1
1 3 3 2

Sample Input 2
1
4
1 3 3 1

Sample Output 2
1 1

Note

In Sample Input 1:

target[0] is included in result by default because it doesn't have two neighbors.
result = [1]

target[1] is greater than both target[0] and target[2], so it is included in result.
result = [1, 3]

target[2] is not greater than its neighbors, so it is not included in result.

target[3] is greater than both target[2] and target[4], so it is included in result.
result = [1, 3, 3]

target[4] is included in result by default because it doesn't have two neighbors.
result = [1, 3, 3, 2]

In Sample Input 2:

target[0] and target[3] are included in result by default.



#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n" // optional, better to avoid redefining endl

void solve()
{
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> v(n);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin >> v[i];
    }
    vector<int> ans;
    ans.push_back(v[0]);
    if (n == 1)
    {
        for (auto it : ans)
        {
            cout << it << " ";
        }
        cout<<endl;
        return;
    }
    for (int i = 1; i < n - 1; i++)
    {
        if (v[i] > max(v[i - 1], v[i + 1]))
        {
            ans.push_back(v[i]);
        }
    }
    ans.push_back(v[n - 1]);
    for (auto it : ans)
    {
        cout << it << " ";
    }
    cout << endl;
}

int main()
{
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--)
    {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}
